ZH: 我昨晚失掉了我的手机。
EN: I lost my phone last night.

ZH: 他失掉了工作，感到很沮丧。
EN: He lost his job and felt very frustrated.

ZH: 她失掉了眼镜，找了好久才找到。
EN: She lost her glasses and it took a long time to find them.

ZH: 他失掉了赛跑比赛的第一名。
EN: He lost the first place in the running competition.

ZH: 小狗在公园里失掉了它的主人。
EN: The puppy lost its owner in the park.

ZH: 昨天失掉了一位亲人，她非常伤心。
EN: She lost a loved one yesterday and she is very sad.

ZH: 这个城市失掉了交通堵塞的问题。
EN: The city lost the problem of traffic congestion.

ZH: 他失掉了所有资金，陷入了困境。
EN: He lost all his funds and fell into a predicament.

ZH: 这家公司失掉了一个重要的合作伙伴。
EN: This company lost an important business partner.

ZH: 这个项目失掉了政府的资助。
EN: This project lost the government's funding.

ZH: 她失掉了在学校的朋友，感到孤单。
EN: She lost her friends at school and felt lonely.

ZH: 他因病失掉了听力。
EN: He lost his hearing due to illness.

ZH: 这个国家失掉了重要的资源。
EN: This country lost important resources.

ZH: 我失掉了看护我的护士。
EN: I lost the nurse who takes care of me.

ZH: 这场比赛他失掉了对手。
EN: He lost to his opponent in this game.

ZH: 他失掉了锻炼身体的机会。
EN: He lost the opportunity to exercise.

ZH: 那个小男孩失掉了最好的朋友。
EN: The little boy lost his best friend.

ZH: 我失掉了这次机会，深感后悔。
EN: I lost this opportunity and deeply regret it.

ZH: 她失掉了读书的动力，不再喜欢学习。
EN: She lost the motivation to study and no longer enjoys learning.

ZH: 这辆车失掉了控制，撞到了树上。
EN: The car lost control and crashed into a tree.
